# ────────────────────────────────────
# CODEOWNERS — Who reviews what
#
# WHY: When a Pull Request changes files in a specific area,
# GitHub automatically assigns the correct reviewer.
# No more "who should review this?" confusion.
#
# HOW IT WORKS:
#   pattern    @owner
#   If a PR touches files matching "pattern", @owner is auto-assigned as reviewer.
#   PR CANNOT be merged until the owner approves.
#
# RULES:
#   - Last matching pattern wins (put specific patterns AFTER general ones)
#   - Use GitHub usernames or team names (@org/team-name)
#   - * means "everything"
# ────────────────────────────────────

# ─── Default: Any file not matched below → Platform team reviews ───
*                                   @platform-team

# ─── Application Code → App developer team ───
# WHY: App developers know the business logic best
src/MedCore.API/                    @app-dev-team
src/MedCore.Tests/                  @app-dev-team

# ─── Infrastructure (Terraform) → Cloud engineer ───
# WHY: Terraform changes can create/destroy Azure resources.
# Only cloud engineers should approve infra changes.
infrastructure/                     @cloud-eng-team

# ─── CI/CD Pipelines → DevOps engineer ───
# WHY: Pipeline changes affect how code gets built and deployed.
# Only DevOps engineers should approve pipeline changes.
.github/workflows/                  @devops-team

# ─── Reusable Action Templates → DevOps + Cloud engineer ───
# WHY: Templates are shared across CI + CD. A tampered template
# could bypass the read-only MI protection.
# Require BOTH DevOps and Cloud engineering review.
.github/actions/                    @devops-team @cloud-eng-team

# ─── Platform Scripts → Cloud admin ───
# WHY: Admin scripts can modify Azure identity, RBAC, and state.
# Only cloud admins should approve these.
platform/                           @cloud-admin

# ─── Documentation → Anyone can review ───
docs/                               @app-dev-team @cloud-eng-team

# ─── Security-sensitive files → Multiple reviewers ───
# WHY: These files affect security posture. Need extra review.
**/Dockerfile                       @devops-team @cloud-eng-team
**/docker-compose*                  @devops-team @cloud-eng-team
.github/workflows/cd.yml           @devops-team @cloud-eng-team
infrastructure/modules/key-vault/   @cloud-eng-team @cloud-admin
